               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0178QMM">Margāḥǝya Qǝddus Mikāʾel</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1730" notAfter="1735">ʾIyasu is mentioned as the reigning
                        king (e.g., <locus target="#11ra">11ra</locus>, 15ra). 
 Ṗeṭros is
                        mentioned as the Patriarch and Krǝstodolu as the Metropolitan (<locus target="#52vb">52vb</locus>). 
 ʾIyasu II was the King of Ethiopia in
                        1730-55 and Krǝstodolu III the Metropolitan of Ethiopia in 1720-35. 
                        The name of Peter VI (Patriarch of Alexandria in 1718-26) is mentioned in
                        the Ms. for unclear reasons, possibly because the scribe was not informed
                        about his demise.</origDate>
                  </origin>
               </history>
